---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LessonShell from "../../components/LessonShell.astro";
import { LESSONS } from "../../data/curriculum";

const lesson = LESSONS.find((l) => l.id === "code-what")!;
---

<Layout title={`${lesson.title} · Learn Claude`} currentId="code-what">
  <main>
    <LessonShell lesson={lesson} hero="code">
      <p>
        Claude Code lives in your terminal. It reads your files, edits them, runs commands —
        with your approval each time something touches your machine.
      </p>

      <div class="diff-grid">
        <div>
          <h3>claude.ai</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Browser chat</li>
            <li>You copy/paste code</li>
            <li>No file access</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Claude Code</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Terminal CLI</li>
            <li>Edits your files directly</li>
            <li>Runs your tests, your dev server, git</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>A typical session</h2>
      <pre>$ cd my-project
$ claude

› the app is crashing on startup, can you find why?

● reading package.json
● running npm start
● error: missing DATABASE_URL

I see — your app needs DATABASE_URL but .env doesn't have one.
Want me to add a placeholder + a clearer startup error?</pre>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Who it's for:</strong> people who write code. If you've never opened a terminal,
        start with claude.ai — come back when you're ready to build something real.
      </div>
    </LessonShell>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .diff-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1.2rem 0 1.6rem;
  }
  .diff-grid > div {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
  }
  .diff-grid h3 { margin: 0 0 0.4rem; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .diff-grid ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.1rem; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  @media (max-width: 600px) { .diff-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
